PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F444A1780665075
OL,3,CChurch minister tells trial Donaldson
OL,4,Cwanted to 'repent'
OL,6,FComplainant A and B have both
OL,7,Fpreviously given evidence at the
OL,8,Fsexual offences trial.
OL,10,FEleanor Donaldson, denies several
OL,11,Fcharges of aiding and abetting her
OL,12,Fhusband's alleged offending.
OL,14,FShe is facing a trial of the facts.
OL,16,FOn Thursday, the court heard evidence
OL,17,Ffrom the husband of Complainant A.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G3/11
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
